the function fetch_url is
  given a url of text, returns the response body as text.
  requires the url scheme is https.
  ensures the result is the response body without modification or yes-no failure.
  benefit cache_hit, fast_path.
  hazard timeout, dns_failure, tls_handshake_error.

the function search_web is
  given a query of text, returns a list of result links as text.
  requires the query is non-empty.
  ensures the results are ordered by the underlying engine relevance.
  benefit index_hit.
  hazard rate_limited, upstream_error.
